1
garages, and any associated grounds, buildings, or appurtenances
1
2
used to operate the races.
2
3
B. No action for nuisance shall be brought against a racing
3
4
facility by an owner of real property within a three-mile radius of
4
5
the racing facility if the developer of the facility obtained all
5
6
permits required for construction, and established a vested right in
6
7
the development of the property or contiguous group of properties
7
8
where the racing facility is located, prior to the date of the owner
8
9
purchasing real property or constructing any building within the
9
10
three-mile radius of the racing facility. Provided, however, such
10
11
liability protection shall not apply if the racing facility fails to
11
12
operate in substantial compliance with federal, state, and local
12
13
laws and regulations applicable to activities occurring at the
13
14
facility.
14
15
SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
